data.title: Events
data.meta_description: With engaging events, compelling lectures, and skill-building workshops, the Penn Libraries is a hub for cultural and educational activity at the University of Pennsylvania. Many library events and exhibitions are open to the public.
data.text:
Aug 20

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

Bookbinding: Drum Leaf Binding

Learn to bind a handmade book using adhesive and stiff yet flexible covers. Use it as a notebook or sketchbook, a gift, or a model for additional handmade books. All supplies provided and no experience needed!

August 20, 2024

2:00pm - 5:00pm

Common Press, basement of Fisher Fine Arts Library

Aug 23

Workshop

Open to Penn Students, Faculty, and Staff

Introduction to Letterpress Printing and Common Press

Learn the fundamentals of setting type and letterpress printing on our Vandercook cylinder presses. We will also discuss alternatives to setting type for printing on the press (photopolymer plates, linoleum, pressure printing). Required as a prerequisite for printing on the Vandercook on independent projects.

August 23, 2024

3:00pm - 5:00pm

Common Press, Fisher Fine Arts Library, Lower Level
